{"type":"message","id":"0502851d","parentId":"9ea112c7","timestamp":"2026-07-11T17:55:32.327Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ccb2d63c04464aaab1161234","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/2026-07-11-your-gpus-are-at-half.md","content":"# 𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗚𝗣𝗨𝘀 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗮𝘁 𝗵𝗮𝗹𝗳 𝗰𝗮𝗽𝗮𝗰𝗶𝘁𝘆. 𝗬𝗼𝘂'𝗿𝗲 𝗯𝗶𝗹𝗹𝗲𝗱 𝗳𝗼𝗿 𝗳𝘂𝗹𝗹.\n\n**Published:** 2026-07-11T17:55:00Z\n**LinkedIn URL:** https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7481768105489379328/\n**Post URN:** urn:li:share:7481768105489379328\n**Format:** image\n**Characters:** 1168\n**Pillar:** (unknown)\n**Image:** /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/boring-agents-1783699220.png\n\n## Post Body\n\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗚𝗣𝗨𝘀 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗮𝘁 𝗵𝗮𝗹𝗳 𝗰𝗮𝗽𝗮𝗰𝗶𝘁𝘆. 𝗬𝗼𝘂'𝗿𝗲 𝗯𝗶𝗹𝗹𝗲𝗱 𝗳𝗼𝗿 𝗳𝘂𝗹𝗹.\n\nNew research from 573 enterprise leaders: 86% of companies running their own GPUs report utilization at 50% or less.\n\nThat's the most expensive hardware in your building sitting half-empty while the invoice stays full.\n\nThe measurement gap makes it worse:\n→ Only 44% rigorously track what their AI compute costs and returns\n→ The rest are estimating — or guessing\n\nMeanwhile 54% had an AI agent security incident or near-miss in the past year. And 71% admit most of their \"agents\" are single-prompt chatbots in trenchcoats — not autonomous multi-step workers.\n\nThe pattern: Enterprises deployed agents first. Controls came later. Now they're retrofitting.\n\nThree moves that matter right now:\n1. Measure GPU utilization before buying more compute\n2. Give every agent its own scoped identity\n3. Govern the business definitions your agents read from\n\nDon't buy another GPU until you know what the ones you have are actually doing.\n\n#AI #EnterpriseAI #GPU #CloudComputing #AIOps\n\n## Performance\n\n*(populated later by linkedin-analytics)*\n\n- **Impressions:** —\n- **Reactions:** —\n- **Comments:** —\n- **Shares:** —\n- **Last checked:** —\n"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/2026-07-11-your-gpus-are-at-half.md\", \"content\": \"# 𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗚𝗣𝗨𝘀 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗮𝘁 𝗵𝗮𝗹𝗳 𝗰𝗮𝗽𝗮𝗰𝗶𝘁𝘆. 𝗬𝗼𝘂'𝗿𝗲 𝗯𝗶𝗹𝗹𝗲𝗱 𝗳𝗼𝗿 𝗳𝘂𝗹𝗹.\\n\\n**Published:** 2026-07-11T17:55:00Z\\n**LinkedIn URL:** https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7481768105489379328/\\n**Post URN:** urn:li:share:7481768105489379328\\n**Format:** image\\n**Characters:** 1168\\n**Pillar:** (unknown)\\n**Image:** /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/boring-agents-1783699220.png\\n\\n## Post Body\\n\\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗚𝗣𝗨𝘀 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗮𝘁 𝗵𝗮𝗹𝗳 𝗰𝗮𝗽𝗮𝗰𝗶𝘁𝘆. 𝗬𝗼𝘂'𝗿𝗲 𝗯𝗶𝗹𝗹𝗲𝗱 𝗳𝗼𝗿 𝗳𝘂𝗹𝗹.\\n\\nNew research from 573 enterprise leaders: 86% of companies running their own GPUs report utilization at 50% or less.\\n\\nThat's the most expensive hardware in your building sitting half-empty while the invoice stays full.\\n\\nThe measurement gap makes it worse:\\n→ Only 44% rigorously track what their AI compute costs and returns\\n→ The rest are estimating — or guessing\\n\\nMeanwhile 54% had an AI agent security incident or near-miss in the past year. And 71% admit most of their \\\"agents\\\" are single-prompt chatbots in trenchcoats — not autonomous multi-step workers.\\n\\nThe pattern: Enterprises deployed agents first. Controls came later. Now they're retrofitting.\\n\\nThree moves that matter right now:\\n1. Measure GPU utilization before buying more compute\\n2. Give every agent its own scoped identity\\n3. Govern the business definitions your agents read from\\n\\nDon't buy another GPU until you know what the ones you have are actually doing.\\n\\n#AI #EnterpriseAI #GPU #CloudComputing #AIOps\\n\\n## Performance\\n\\n*(populated later by linkedin-analytics)*\\n\\n- **Impressions:** —\\n- **Reactions:** —\\n- **Comments:** —\\n- **Shares:** —\\n- **Last checked:** —\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":